    "definitionDraft": "Autonomous driving (AI view) uses a single/unified deep model to map raw sensor inputs end-to-end to vehicle planning and control, replacing the hand-written perception→prediction→planning→control pipeline. Three frontiers: end-to-end learning, generative driving world models, and VLA/large-model-driven driving.",
    "whyNow": "Tesla FSD v12 replaced ~300k lines of C++ control code with neural networks (\"photons in, controls out\"); Wayve’s GAIA world models and Waymo’s EMMA push generative/VLM-driven driving. The end-to-end paradigm is Karpathy’s \"Software 2.0\" at its most thorough in driving.",
    "useBoundary": "Focus on AI methodology frontiers in autonomous driving (end-to-end, driving world models, VLA-for-driving). Exclude general-purpose robotics/VLA (embodied-ai), whole-vehicle reviews and policy/regulation."
  },
